# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# projects/.gitignore
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The outer clappie repo tracks projects/ by default. Quick apps, static
# sites, and one-off builds get committed normally — that's fine.
#
# BUT: if a project has its own .git/ (cloned repos, serious standalone
# projects), it MUST be listed here. Otherwise the outer repo sees it as
# untracked junk and git operations (especially `git clean`) can destroy it.
#
# Rule: if it has its own git, add it here.
#
# Example:
#   my-cloned-repo/
#   big-serious-project/
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
clappie-docs-website/
oh-zero-website/
pi-hole-management/
backtester/
